-- German Union Ver.di Calls for Bank Strikes Today, DPA Reports
-- B y   A n n e t t e   W e i s b a c h
-- 2012-04-30T07:11:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-30/german-union-ver-di-calls-for-bank-strikes-today-dpa-reports.html
German labor union Ver.di called on
bank employees in certain areas of the country to go on strike
today before a third round of pay negotiations starting May 3,
DPA said, citing Ver.di spokeswoman Martina Soennichsen.  Munich-based employees of  UniCredit SpA (UCG)  as well as staff of
 Commerzbank AG (CBK)  and NordLB based in Bremen and Hanover are called
to go on strike today, DAP said. Ver.di is demanding a 6 percent
wage increase for 220,000 workers and employers, DPA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Annette Weisbach in Frankfurt at 
 aweisbach1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
